This paper deals with the performance analysis of UAV-to-UAV (U2U) communications in cellular networks, which involves the study of wireless communication channels, signal processing, and network protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of power control mechanisms and antenna patterns, which are related to information theory and signal processing, respectively, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia) likely categories as well. The paper also considers the interplay between different links and the impact of interference, which are related to system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of UAV communications, which is related to cryptography and network security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category as well.
